; Regression test for issue #1692: Output breaks accounting equation
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1692
;
; Inferred balancing amounts whose magnitude was less than the
; commodity's default display precision (0 digits for a newly
; encountered commodity like Y below) would compare equal to zero via
; amount_t::is_zero(), even though the value was non-zero at the
; recovered cost precision.  Balance and register output then silently
; omitted the balancing posting, violating double-entry accounting.
;
; The fix flags the inferred amount with BIGINT_COST_PREC via
; set_cost_precision() and teaches amount_t::is_zero() to respect the
; widened precision implied by the flag.  BIGINT_COST_PREC must not
; propagate through addition/subtraction, or running-total residuals
; would inherit it (see issue #717 rounding adjustments).

2018-01-01 * Foo
    Assets:A                    2 X @ 0.2 Y
    Assets:B

test bal
                 2 X
               Y-0.4  Assets
                 2 X    A
               Y-0.4    B
--------------------
                 2 X
               Y-0.4
end test

test reg
18-Jan-01 Foo                   Assets:A                        2 X          2 X
                                Assets:B                      Y-0.4          2 X
                                                                           Y-0.4
end test

test print
2018/01/01 * Foo
    Assets:A                                     2 X @ Y0.2
    Assets:B
end test
